    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="post-body-wrap">
    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">

        <div class="snippet-answer">
          <p><strong>GBP verification</strong> is the mandatory process where Google confirms your business exists at the claimed address and you are authorised to manage the Google Business Profile listing. Verified businesses unlock full profile control, Map Pack eligibility, review management, and access to GBP Insights. Google verified over 7 million businesses in 2022 alone.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="term-meta-strip">
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Postcard timeline</div>
            <div class="tms-value">5–14 business days</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Category</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Local SEO</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Map Pack click share</div>
            <div class="tms-value">42% of local clicks</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Difficulty</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Beginner</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lede-p">An unverified GBP is like a shop with the lights off — it technically exists, but customers cannot interact with it and Google will not surface it reliably. Verification is the first step in every local SEO strategy.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is GBP verification?</h2>
        <p>GBP verification is Google's gatekeeping mechanism for local search. Before granting full access to a Google Business Profile, Google requires proof that the claiming entity is the actual business — not a competitor trying to hijack the listing, not a scammer creating a fake address, and not a duplicate of an already-verified profile.</p>
        <p>The verification process typically involves sending a code to the business's physical location (by postcard, phone, or email) and having the claimant enter that code in the GBP dashboard. For businesses in categories that experience high fraud rates, Google has introduced video verification — requiring the owner to record a real-time walkthrough of the business premises.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">Why verification matters for local rankings</div>
          <p>Unverified listings rarely appear in the Map Pack — the 3-result block at the top of Google's local search results that captures 42% of all local search clicks. Verification is not a ranking signal by itself, but it unlocks the profile management features (reviews, posts, photos) that are direct ranking inputs.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="why-it-matters">Why GBP verification matters</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Map Pack eligibility.</strong> Unverified listings are systematically excluded from the 3-pack that dominates local search result pages. Verified listings compete for all three slots.</li>
          <li><strong>Full profile control.</strong> Only verified owners can respond to reviews, update business hours, publish posts, add photos, and access the complete GBP dashboard.</li>
          <li><strong>Access to GBP Insights.</strong> Verification unlocks the analytics dashboard showing search queries, photo views, direction requests, and call metrics — the data you need to measure local SEO performance.</li>
          <li><strong>Hijacking prevention.</strong> A verified listing is much harder for a competitor or malicious actor to claim. Without verification, anyone can request ownership.</li>
          <li><strong>Trust signals to customers.</strong> Verified listings display a checkmark on Google Maps that signals to users the business has been confirmed as legitimate.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How GBP verification works — step by step</h2>
        <p>Verification follows three stages regardless of which method you use.</p>

        <div class="url-flow">
          <span class="uf-comment"># Step 1: Claim or create your profile</span><br>
          Visit <span class="uf-new">business.google.com</span> and search for your business<br>
          If found: click <span class="uf-label">Claim this business</span><br>
          If not found: click <span class="uf-label">Add your business to Google</span><br>
          Enter business name, category, address<br>
          <br>
          <span class="uf-comment"># Step 2: Choose verification method</span><br>
          Available options depend on business type and history<br>
          <span class="uf-label">Postcard</span> · <span class="uf-label">Phone</span> · <span class="uf-label">Email</span> · <span class="uf-label">Video</span> · <span class="uf-label">Instant</span><br>
          <br>
          <span class="uf-comment"># Step 3: Enter code and confirm</span><br>
          Enter PIN from postcard / call / email in your GBP dashboard<br>
          Google reviews and activates the listing: <span class="uf-status">usually within 24 hours</span>
        </div>

        <h2 id="types">Types of GBP verification — which method is right for you</h2>

